      "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
      "patch_summary": "This patch modifies the Linux kernel's page allocation mechanism to allow high-priority non-blocking allocations to use existing MIGRATE_HIGHATOMIC reserves on the buddy fastpath without growing them. The patch tightens the criteria for reserving pageblocks so that growth only occurs in the slowpath, and introduces a new function gfp_to_alloc_flags_nonblocking() to enable this behavior. This change improves performance by reducing the number of highatomic misses observed during a UDP receive workload."
